@startuml
!include ../../style.puml

title The Three Performance Zones

' [step1 {"name":"Zone 1: The Safe Zone"}]
rectangle "Utilization: 0% to 80%" as safe #LightGreen
note bottom of safe
  **Predictable & Fast**
  Response time is stable.
  Queues empty almost instantly.
  Lq < 5
end note
' [/step1]

' [step2 {"name":"Zone 2: The Transition Zone"}]
rectangle "Utilization: 80% to 95%" as warn #LightYellow
safe -> warn

note bottom of warn
  **Queuing Begins**
  Response time rises noticeably.
  Bursts cause brief saturation.
  Lq grows non-linearly.
end note
' [/step2]

' [step3 {"name":"Zone 3: The Hockey Stick (Saturation)"}]
rectangle "Utilization: > 95%" as danger #FFCCCC
warn -> danger

note bottom of danger
  **Exponential Explosion**
  Waiting time vastly exceeds service time.
  Small increases in load cause massive delays.
  System is effectively saturated.
end note
' [/step3]

@enduml
